      "content": "Hey, can you help me write a rejection email? It's for a candidate who made it all the way to the final round for a Senior Dev role here in Austin, but we ended up going with someone else who had a bit more experience with Kubernetes. I want it to sound professional but not like a robot, u know? Like, acknowledge they did a great job in the interviews so they actually feel respected. Thanks.",
